<Page x:Class="MemoryTrainer.Misc.HelpText"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
      xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
      xmlns:local="clr-namespace:MemoryTrainer.Misc"
      mc:Ignorable="d" 
      d:DesignHeight="450" d:DesignWidth="800"
      Title="HelpText">

    <Page.Resources>
        <Style x:Key="titleParagraph" TargetType="Paragraph">
            <Setter Property="FontSize" Value="16"/>
            <Setter Property="FontWeight" Value="DemiBold"/>
        </Style>

        <Style x:Key="defaultParagraph" TargetType="Paragraph">
            <Setter Property="FontSize" Value="14"/>
        </Style>
    </Page.Resources>

    
    
    <FlowDocumentReader IsTwoPageViewEnabled="False" IsFindEnabled="False" >
        <FlowDocument>
            <Section>
                <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource titleParagraph}">
                    Welcome!
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource defaultParagraph}">
                    This tool contains small games for improving the memory. It is inspired by the book Remember it! written by Nelson Dellis. If you need any hints or strategies, 
                    please consult this book. At the moment, there is only one game available and more games are already in preparation. This is a spare time project and it is done when it is done.
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource defaultParagraph}">
                    Enjoy the games and hopefully you find it useful.
                </Paragraph>
            </Section>
            <Section>
                <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource titleParagraph}">PAO Card Game</Paragraph>
                <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource defaultParagraph}">
                    I thought about creating such a game for a long time. Everybody knows playing cards and if you can recall a playing card in your memory journey then you can recall other content as well. 
                    This games uses the PAO (Person Action Object) strategy, but you can use any other you prefer. Please follow the instructions in the game and good luck.
                </Paragraph>
            </Section>
        </FlowDocument>
    </FlowDocumentReader>
</Page>
